<br>
Now the two things wrong with this movie were the ending and all of the lulls.<br>
<br>
The ending did end on a cliffhanger, but not on a high note.  There was no closure for someone who has only seen the movies.  To say that someone should have to read the book to get it is unfair.  If you are going to make something into a movie, then the movie become the representation of the story.  The movie needs to do a good job at being a movie, not just a re-iteration of the book.<br>
<br>
The lulls.  We do this.  We walk.  We do this.  Walk more.  At some point the walking scenes could have been integrated with the talking scenes and then there would have been more of a steady flow.  Something that is very important to a 3 hour movie. <p> "There is a theory which states that if ever anybody discovers exactly what the Universe is for and why it is here, it will instantly disappear and be replaced by something even more bizarre and inexplicable. There is another theory which states that this has already happened."

