All-in-all...I am quite satisfied with the movie.  There have been a couple attempts at creating this series of books...and to be percectly frank...they all sucked.  Really.  The animation was crap...and...the animated series I saw this is the order in which they made the movies:  Hobbit, Return of the King.  That is it.  All of a sudden you see Sam pounding on a door of a huge castle trying to get to Frodo.  You dont know how they got there...what they're doing...or anything.  It made me sick.  They apparently made another movie...though I never saw it.  I heard nothing good from it so I didnt.  I did see a clip of the sucky animation, however. <br>
<br>
They did a superb job with that movie.  They had a huge potential to screw up big time...and they made a movie, for the most part, true to the book.  The graphics were great, and it wasnt a movie tht was made just for the sole puprose of saying &quot;look what we can do&quot;...the computer stuff was really integrated into the movie well.  As for someone's comment about falling asleep...well...I saw a lot of action...perhaps you shouldnt have fallen asleep.  As for the first being the most exciting part...&quot;welcome..to my birthday party....etc...bunch of talking&quot;...well if you find that exciting, I could send you a very large phone-book that you can read!  <br>
<br>
Why dont we try and see all that these people DID do right...then the minimal tidbits some people seem so upset about...will seem like nothing. <p><center> -No, Mom!  I don't need college.  I'm going to follow my dream, and become a clown!-<center>
